post_text: This year Sigourney PTO will be offering student school supply kits with prices ranging from $20-$50 depending upon what teachers require at each grade level. Order forms will be sent out mid April and orders/payments will need to be placed by May 24th with a delivery date of Open House Night for the 2019-2020 school year. Our goal is to provide families with a method of purchasing supplies at a reasonable cost. Parents this is an option but aren’t required to participate. We are working in collaboration with Bailey’s Office Supply in Ottumwa, Iowa to make this possible. We will send out forms as soon as possible but wanted to make parents aware of a possible expense for the future.

post_text:
Sigourney PTO sponsors many events and purchases materials for the kiddos to be used in the classroom. We typically have only one form of fundraisers that we do, which is the clothing web store. We make a minimal amount of money off of that because we try to keep our prices low so families can afford Sigourney apparel. As a new fundraiser for Sigourney PTO, we are going to give schoolstore.com a try here at the end of the year. Students will bring home packets on Friday, March 2nd explaining the guidelines for online registration. Please watch for the packet. Students can earn a prize for returning the packet on Monday.

The great thing about this fundraiser is that students won't be selling door to door. There will be no collection of money and no delivery of products. The schoolstore.com website lets people select stores that they typically shop from. PTO will receive a percentage of money back to help sponsor events during the school year. This will allow us to provide materials for kids to use in the classroom, and all parents have to do is shop from home. It's a win, win!

post_text: It's the start to a new school year, and that means PTO is in full force! We will be installing flashing lights on the two stop signs on Hwy. 149 and also putting in a new water fountain with a water bottle filler! We have lots of events planned for the year but we need lots of help. Make sure you get those volunteer sheets filled out. There are lots of ways to help out even if you can't make the meetings :). Grandparent's Night and the Halloween party will be the first couple events with a savage apparel store to open sometime in November.
